29/12/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Police announced on Monday (December 28th) that US investigators from the FBI are helping them search for the stolen remains of late Cypriot President Tassos Papadopoulos. Police spokesperson Michalis Katsounotos said an FBI agent attached to the US Embassy in Greece visited the island last week. Authorities in Israel and Greece have offered to help as well. The remains of Papadopoulos -- who died on December 12th 2008 -- were stolen on December 11th from a cemetery in the village of Deftera, near Nicosia. (AFP, AP - 28/12/09)
